    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276885\">Kenji Maillard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229111-general/topic/.22Diagonal.20Yoneda.22/near/262626520\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm afraid a lot of categories would end up being called <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"bold\">Morphism</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\textbf{Morphism}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textbf\">Morphism</span></span></span></span></span>...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>... which would of course be abbreviated to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"bold\">Morph</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\textbf{Morph}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textbf\">Morph</span></span></span></span></span>, which is nice because morph is also a verb, so we could write papers in pure syntax, from a one word lexicon, like <a href=\"https://isotropic.org/papers/chicken.pdf\">https://isotropic.org/papers/chicken.pdf</a></p>",
